This paper discusses the security implications of software debloating, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also proposes new metrics for assessing the security impact of software debloating, which falls under programming languages (cs.PL) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses a tool to efficiently calculate these metrics, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG).
